        <marginalia hand="English_secretary" anchor_text="quid quisque nostrum de se ipse loquatur, non est san&egrave; requirendum: boni viri iudicent, id est maximi momenti &amp; ponderis">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Quid quisq[ue] de seip[s]o loquatur no[n] est san&egrave; req[ui]rendum: boni viri iudicent, id est maximi mome[n]ti et ponderis.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                What each of us says about himself is not really the question. Let good men form their judgment! That is of the greatest importance and weight [Loeb 309, 251].
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
